    <para id="import-auto-id2919469">The final temperature is about 6% greater than the original temperature, so the final pressure is about 6% greater as well. Note that <emphasis effect="italics">absolute</emphasis> pressure and <emphasis effect="italics">absolute</emphasis> temperature must be used in the ideal gas law.</para>
