    </exercise><exercise id="fs-id2094656" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2094657">    <para id="import-auto-id2637302">In the text, it was shown that <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>N</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">/</m:mo><m:mi>V</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>68</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>25</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:msup><m:mtext>m</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>  for gas at STP. (a) Show that this quantity is equivalent to <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>N</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">/</m:mo><m:mi>V</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>68</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>19</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:msup><m:mtext>cm</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mi>,</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>  as stated. (b) About how many atoms are there in one <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mtext>μm</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math> (a cubic micrometer) at STP? (c) What does your answer to part (b) imply about the separation of atoms and molecules? </para></problem></exercise>
